721051f-a.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 68th Street
721051f-a.text:
Normal College for Women (later known as Hunter College), rear
view, Lexington Avenue, west side, from b8th to 69th Streets.
The square tower, in the left background, is on the S.E. corner
of Park Avenue and t9th Street. The building as here shown is
brand new.
In the foreground is the space later to be occupied by Thomas
Hunter Hall. At the time of this picture Lexington Avenue had
not been cut through.
1872.
Ewing Galloway.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
